Useful text sometime?

DefaultValueConfigItem.java leads to EditCustomFieldDefaults!default.jspa
actions.xml leads to EditCustomFieldDefaults and editcustomfield-default.jsp
editcustomfield-default.jsp leads to EditCustomFieldDefaults.getCustomFieldHtml()

getCustomFieldHtml adds defaultScreen=true and objectValue=CustomFieldType.getDefaultValue(config) to what becomes displayParameters in the Velocity context and then leads to CustomFieldTypeModuleDescriptor.java.getEditDefaultHtml()

Which says that there can be a Velocity resource edit-default for the HTML used for the editing a default screen
The parameters it uses are the usual ones from CustomFieldUtils.buildParams such as value and CustomFieldType.getVelocityParameters() and configs


